# LESSON 3 requests. Server: npm run lesson3  (or lesson3:scaffold)
#
# This lesson only reads data OUT, so the one request here is a GET. Sending
# data in was lesson 2.

@host = http://localhost:3300


### The endpoint you write in step 1
# Before step 1 is written this returns 404. Worth sending first, so the 404
# is a known state rather than a surprise later.
#
# Once it works, this shows the exact JSON the React page will receive, which
# is the thing to get right before writing any component code.

GET {{host}}/get-all-animals
